<p class="title">Details</p>

<p>The SOG M37 Combat knife is nicknamed the Seal Pup
because it is the preferred knife of the U.S. Navy Seals. You
always begin with one knife (or more if you select them in
teamplay). The knife can be used in standard slashing mode where
you must be very close to your enemy but one good slash will
usually be enough to kill them outright, if you want a ranged
attack you can switch to throwing mode, the knife can then be
thrown at your enemy and if it hits it will tear through kevlar and
flesh like paper doing tremendous amounts of damage, the only
problem is that the knife flies a lot slower than a bullet and
gravity causes it to arc downwards as it flies. If you plan on
throwing knives you can pick up extras from dead bodies or from the
walls and floor where they have been thrown.</p>

